http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Uber-hackathon/article13996046.ece

Cab aggregator Uber conducted a hackathon in the city on Tuesday with the aim of developing new features. “This is the first time ever we are doing a hackathon in Asia,” said Saad Ahmed, Uber India Business Development Lead. It will hold the 2nd hackathon in India in Delhi on January 15. Uber also announced the global launch of its API (Application Programming Interface) for developers, ‘Uber Trip Experience’. It allows third-party applications to serve notifications, content, music or advertisement during trips. Twelve teams, who are the company’s partners, participated in the hackathon.